export const meta = {
  name: 'milne33-substep1-api-map',
  description: 'Map the four mathlib API areas needed to assemble Milne 3.3 difference map',
  phases: [{ title: 'Investigate', detail: '4 parallel mathlib-API investigations' }],
}

const MATHLIB = '/home/Axel/LeanAlgebraicGeometry/.shared-packages/mathlib'
const PROJ = '/home/Axel/LeanAlgebraicGeometry-Horizon/MainProjects/Algebraic-Jacobian-Challenge'

const SCHEMA = {
  type: 'object',
  additionalProperties: false,
  properties: {
    area: { type: 'string' },
    keyDeclarations: {
      type: 'array',
      items: {
        type: 'object',
        additionalProperties: false,
        properties: {
          name: { type: 'string', description: 'fully qualified Lean name' },
          signature: { type: 'string', description: 'the exact statement/type copied verbatim from source' },
          file: { type: 'string' },
          line: { type: 'integer' },
          isInstance: { type: 'boolean', description: 'true if it is an instance (auto-synthesizable)' },
          note: { type: 'string' },
        },
        required: ['name', 'signature', 'file', 'note'],
      },
    },
    recommendedSnippet: { type: 'string', description: 'concrete Lean code snippet the caller can paste, using the found declarations' },
    caveats: { type: 'string', description: 'gotchas, defeq walls, universe issues, missing lemmas that must be proven by hand' },
    confidence: { type: 'string', enum: ['high', 'medium', 'low'] },
  },
  required: ['area', 'keyDeclarations', 'recommendedSnippet', 'caveats', 'confidence'],
}

const common = 'You are investigating mathlib v4.31 source to map a precise API area. Mathlib is at ' + MATHLIB + ' (grep/read its Mathlib/ subtree for ground truth). The consuming project is at ' + PROJ + '. You may also use the lean LSP MCP tools via ToolSearch (query select:mcp__lean-lsp__lean_loogle,mcp__lean-lsp__lean_hover_info,mcp__lean-lsp__lean_local_search) but prefer grep/Read of mathlib source. Return EXACT declaration names, verbatim signatures copied from source, file paths, and line numbers. Do NOT guess names; verify each against the source line. Your final output is consumed programmatically as data, not shown to a human.'

phase('Investigate')

const results = await parallel([
  () => agent(common + '\n\nAREA: Smooth implies GeometricallyReduced (and toward GeometricallyIntegral) for a scheme morphism over a field.\n\nCONTEXT: In ' + PROJ + '/AlgebraicJacobian/Albanese/CodimOneExtension.lean, theorem indeterminacy_pure_codim_one_into_grpScheme has, for X : Over (Spec (.of kbar)) with kbar an algebraically closed field: [Smooth X.hom] [GeometricallyIrreducible X.hom] [IsSeparated X.hom] [LocallyOfFiniteType X.hom] [IsIntegral X.left] [IsReduced X.left]. GOAL: conclude IsIntegral (pullback X.hom X.hom). Memory says the one genuine new small lemma is: Smooth f implies GeometricallyReduced f (mathlib v4.31 supposedly has only the converse, e.g. smooth_of_grpObj style).\n\nInvestigate and report:\n1. Exact name + verbatim signature of the morphism-property GeometricallyReduced (and GeometricallyIntegral, GeometricallyIrreducible, GeometricallyConnected) for scheme morphisms. Look under ' + MATHLIB + '/Mathlib/AlgebraicGeometry/Geometrically/ (Reduced.lean, Integral.lean, Irreducible.lean, Connected.lean).\n2. Does mathlib already have Smooth implies GeometricallyReduced in any form (instance, lemma, or via smooth implies geometrically regular/reduced fibers)? grep GeometricallyReduced, Smooth, smooth across Geometrically/ and Morphisms/Smooth*.lean. Also RingHom.Smooth / Algebra.Smooth implies geometrically reduced/regular (Mathlib/RingTheory/Smooth/...). Report the closest existing lemma and whether it needs an algebraically-closed or perfect base.\n3. How GeometricallyIntegral is characterized (e.g. geometricallyIntegral_iff = GeometricallyReduced and GeometricallyIrreducible, or similar).\n4. recommendedSnippet: how to conclude GeometricallyReduced X.hom from [Smooth X.hom] over an algebraically closed field, or precisely what sub-lemma must be hand-proved and its cleanest route.', { label: 'geomReduced', phase: 'Investigate', schema: SCHEMA }),

  () => agent(common + '\n\nAREA: IsIntegral (pullback f f) — product of an integral scheme with itself over an algebraically closed field.\n\nCONTEXT: X : Over (Spec (.of kbar)), kbar : Field, IsAlgClosed kbar, with [Smooth X.hom] [GeometricallyIrreducible X.hom] [IsSeparated X.hom] [LocallyOfFiniteType X.hom] [IsIntegral X.left] [IsReduced X.left]. Need an instance/term IsIntegral (pullback X.hom X.hom). Memory pointer: Geometrically/Integral.lean:108.\n\nInvestigate and report:\n1. Read ' + MATHLIB + '/Mathlib/AlgebraicGeometry/Geometrically/Integral.lean fully (esp. near line 108). Report every lemma concluding IsIntegral or GeometricallyIntegral of a pullback/fibre product with exact signature + hypotheses (e.g. GeometricallyIntegral.pullback, or IsIntegral (pullback f g) from GeometricallyIntegral f + IsIntegral codomain).\n2. Exact chain from my hypotheses to IsIntegral (pullback X.hom X.hom): both factors are X over Spec kbar. Likely GeometricallyIntegral X.hom (from GeometricallyReduced + GeometricallyIrreducible + IsIntegral) then pullback over an algebraically closed field is integral. Report precise lemma names.\n3. Also check Geometrically/Irreducible.lean and Reduced.lean for pullback-stability lemmas (base change of geometrically irreducible; product of geometrically irreducible/reduced).\n4. recommendedSnippet: a haveI/have chain yielding IsIntegral (pullback X.hom X.hom) assuming GeometricallyReduced X.hom is available. Note every instance that must be supplied.', { label: 'productIntegral', phase: 'Investigate', schema: SCHEMA }),

  () => agent(common + '\n\nAREA: Difference morphism d = ((g,h) to g times h-inverse) : G tensor G to G for a group object, in the cartesian-monoidal category Over (Spec kbar), and extracting its underlying scheme morphism.\n\nCONTEXT: G : Over (Spec (.of kbar)) with [GrpObj G] (mathlib CategoryTheory.GrpObj, ' + MATHLIB + '/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Monoidal/Grp_.lean:43). C = Over (Spec (.of kbar)) is cartesian monoidal. Need the division morphism d : G tensor G to G representing (g,h) to g times h-inverse (Milne uses f(x) times f(y)-inverse). Then need d.left : (G tensor G).left to G.left, and that (G tensor G).left = pullback G.hom G.hom (via CategoryTheory.Over.tensorObj_left), and d.w (the over-Spec triangle).\n\nInvestigate and report:\n1. In ' + MATHLIB + '/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Monoidal/Cartesian/Grp_.lean: the group structure on hom-sets (memory cites Monoidal/Cartesian/Grp.lean:59,66, likely an instance named Hom.group or similar). Exact instance name giving Group (X to G) and/or a Div/HDiv, with verbatim signature. Confirm one can write (fst / snd : G tensor G to G) for fst snd : G tensor G to G, and that division equals pointwise mul of fst with inv of snd.\n2. The two projections G tensor G to G in a cartesian monoidal category: exact names + signatures (CartesianMonoidalCategory.fst / .snd) from ' + MATHLIB + '/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Monoidal/Cartesian/Basic.lean.\n3. Check GrpObj.conj / GrpObj.commutator / any GrpObj.div in Grp_.lean — is there a ready-made div : G tensor G to G = mul of (fst, snd then inv)? If yes report it; else report how to build it via lift (fst) (snd then inv) then MonObj.mul, or via fst / snd using the hom-group.\n4. Over category: ' + MATHLIB + '/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Monoidal/Cartesian/Over.lean — confirm the exact name+signature of the lemma (G tensor H).left = pullback G.hom H.hom. And how (d : X to Y in Over S).left and .w work (Comma/Over.Hom fields, CommaMorphism.left, Over.w).\n5. recommendedSnippet: given [GrpObj G] on G : Over (Spec kbar), produce d : G tensor G to G and its .left : pullback G.hom G.hom to G.left, and how to discharge the over-Spec condition from d.w.', { label: 'diffMorphism', phase: 'Investigate', schema: SCHEMA }),

  () => agent(common + '\n\nAREA: Openness of the first projection: IsOpenMap (pullback.fst X.hom X.hom).base for X.hom smooth over a field.\n\nCONTEXT: X : Over (Spec (.of kbar)), [Smooth X.hom] [LocallyOfFiniteType X.hom]. Need IsOpenMap (pullback.fst X.hom X.hom).base (topological openness of the first projection of the self-product) to feed RationalMap.precomp. Memory chain: Smooth X.hom implies Smooth (pullback.fst X.hom X.hom) [Smooth.lean:187] implies Flat + LocallyOfFinitePresentation implies UniversallyOpen [UniversallyOpen.lean:145] implies IsOpenMap.\n\nInvestigate and report:\n1. In ' + MATHLIB + '/Mathlib/AlgebraicGeometry/Morphisms/Smooth.lean (around line 187): the instance/lemma that Smooth is stable under base change/pullback. Exact name + signature. Does Smooth (pullback.fst f g) synthesize as an instance from [Smooth g]? Report exact names (MorphismProperty.IsStableUnderBaseChange, pullback_fst, etc).\n2. Smooth implies Flat and Smooth implies LocallyOfFinitePresentation (or LocallyOfFiniteType): exact instance names.\n3. In ' + MATHLIB + '/Mathlib/AlgebraicGeometry/Morphisms/UniversallyOpen.lean (around line 145): the lemma giving UniversallyOpen from Flat + LocallyOfFinitePresentation. Exact name + signature + hypotheses.\n4. From UniversallyOpen f to IsOpenMap f.base: exact lemma name (e.g. UniversallyOpen.isOpenMap, or an instance).\n5. recommendedSnippet: exact have hopen : IsOpenMap (pullback.fst X.hom X.hom).base := ... term/tactic block, marking which steps are instance-synthesis vs explicit application. Note any missing hypothesis (LocallyOfFinitePresentation vs LocallyOfFiniteType, QuasiCompact) that must be added.', { label: 'openness', phase: 'Investigate', schema: SCHEMA }),
])

return results

