export const meta = {
  name: 'verify-difference-map',
  description: 'Adversarially verify the Milne 3.3 difference-map construction and its blueprint',
  phases: [{ title: 'Verify', detail: 'soundness/Milne + blueprint/DAG' }],
}

const PROJ = '/home/Axel/LeanAlgebraicGeometry-Horizon/MainProjects/Algebraic-Jacobian-Challenge'
const MATHLIB = '/home/Axel/LeanAlgebraicGeometry/.shared-packages/mathlib'

const SCHEMA = {
  type: 'object',
  additionalProperties: false,
  properties: {
    verdict: { type: 'string', enum: ['SOUND', 'BUG_FOUND', 'UNSURE'] },
    findings: {
      type: 'array',
      items: {
        type: 'object',
        additionalProperties: false,
        properties: {
          claim: { type: 'string', description: 'the specific thing checked' },
          result: { type: 'string', enum: ['ok', 'defect', 'concern'] },
          detail: { type: 'string', description: 'evidence: file:line + reasoning' },
        },
        required: ['claim', 'result', 'detail'],
      },
    },
    summary: { type: 'string' },
  },
  required: ['verdict', 'findings', 'summary'],
}

phase('Verify')

const results = await parallel([
  () => agent('You are an adversarial verifier. Try to find a SOUNDNESS or FAITHFULNESS bug in a newly-landed Lean construction; default to skepticism.\n\nFILES (read them):\n- ' + PROJ + '/AlgebraicJacobian/Albanese/DifferenceMap.lean (the new construction)\n- ' + PROJ + '/AlgebraicJacobian/Albanese/RationalMapPrecomp.lean and RationalMapProd.lean (the bricks it uses; read the signatures of precomp, precomp_compHom, precomp_hom_toRationalMap, prod, prod_compHom_fst/snd/over)\n- ' + PROJ + '/AlgebraicJacobian/Albanese/CodimOneExtension.lean lines 1639-1721 (the theorem indeterminacy_pure_codim_one_into_grpScheme this feeds, and Milne 3.3 substep description)\nMathlib for group-object API: ' + MATHLIB + '/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Monoidal/Cartesian/Grp_.lean (Hom.group: f/g = f*g⁻¹, mul = lift f g ≫ μ, inv = f ≫ ι) and Monoidal/Cartesian/Over.lean (tensorObj_left, Over.w).\n\nATTACK these specific claims; for each say ok/defect/concern with evidence:\n1. ORIENTATION: Is CategoryTheory.GrpObj.diff G = fst G G / snd G G pointwise (g,h) ↦ g·h⁻¹, and NOT g⁻¹·h or h·g⁻¹ or h⁻¹·g? Work it out from Hom.group (div_eq_mul_inv, mul_def = lift ≫ μ, inv_def = ·≫ι). Does this match Milne substep 1 Φ(x,y)=f(x)·f(y)⁻¹ once composed with prod(f∘pr₁, f∘pr₂)?\n2. grpObjDiffLeft G : pullback G.hom G.hom ⟶ G.left is DEFINED as (GrpObj.diff G).left via a type-ascription (defeq (G⊗G).left = pullback G.hom G.hom). Is this a genuine identity (no data smuggled, kernel-checkable), or could it mis-associate the pullback legs?\n3. grpObjDiffLeft_comp_hom := Over.w (GrpObj.diff G). Over.w says φ.left ≫ g.hom = f.hom. Is the lemma statement (grpObjDiffLeft G ≫ G.hom = pullback.fst G.hom G.hom ≫ G.hom) the correct instance, and is (G⊗G).hom really pullback.fst G.hom G.hom ≫ G.hom (tensorObj_hom)?\n4. differenceRationalMap: the ha/hb proofs. ha: (f.precomp pr₁).compHom G.hom = (pr₁ ≫ X.hom).toRat via precomp_compHom+hover+precomp_hom_toRationalMap. hb: same target but for pr₂, closed by pullback.condition. Are ha/hb proving NON-VACUOUS, correct over-k̄ facts (not e.g. a trivially-true statement due to a defeq collapse)? Is passing the SAME sX = pr₁≫X.hom for both a and b correct (b uses pr₂, and pr₁≫X.hom = pr₂≫X.hom by pullback.condition)?\n5. differenceRationalMap_compHom_over: is the conclusion (Φ.compHom G.hom = (pr₁≫X.hom).toRat) the right notion of "Φ is a k̄-rational map", and does the proof (simp differenceRationalMap; compHom_compHom; grpObjDiffLeft_comp_hom; prod_compHom_over) actually establish it without gaps?\n\nOutput data only.', { label: 'soundness', phase: 'Verify', schema: SCHEMA }),

  () => agent('You are an adversarial verifier of BLUEPRINT faithfulness and DAG consistency. Be skeptical.\n\nFILES:\n- ' + PROJ + '/blueprint/src/chapters/Albanese_CodimOneExtension.tex — the new nodes are def:grpObj_diff, lem:grpObjDiffLeft_comp_hom, def:rationalMap_difference, lem:rationalMap_difference_over (search for them), plus they are added to the \\uses of the proof of lem:milne_codim1_indeterminacy (search "Following Milne\'s proof of Lemma~3.3").\n- ' + PROJ + '/AlgebraicJacobian/Albanese/DifferenceMap.lean — the Lean decls the \\lean{} keys must name EXACTLY: CategoryTheory.GrpObj.diff, AlgebraicGeometry.grpObjDiffLeft, AlgebraicGeometry.grpObjDiffLeft_comp_hom, AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.RationalMap.differenceRationalMap, AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.RationalMap.differenceRationalMap_compHom_over.\n\nCHECK, each ok/defect/concern with evidence:\n1. Every \\lean{...} key in the four new nodes names a declaration that ACTUALLY EXISTS with that exact fully-qualified name in DifferenceMap.lean (grep to confirm). Flag any typo/mismatch.\n2. Every \\label referenced in the new nodes\' \\uses and in the milne proof \\uses (def:rationalMap_precomp, def:rationalMap_prod, def:grpObj_diff, lem:grpObjDiffLeft_comp_hom, def:rationalMap_difference, lem:rationalMap_difference_over, lem:rationalMap_precomp_compHom, lem:rationalMap_precomp_hom, lem:rationalMap_prod_proj) has a matching \\label somewhere in the blueprint/src/chapters/*.tex. Flag any dangling reference (a \\uses to a non-existent \\label).\n3. FAITHFULNESS: does each blueprint node\'s stated math match what the named Lean decl proves? Especially: def:grpObj_diff claims (g,h)↦g·h⁻¹; lem:rationalMap_difference_over claims Φ∘(G→Spec k̄) = pr₁∘(X→Spec k̄). Read the Lean signatures and confirm the prose is not overclaiming or misstating.\n4. Are the new nodes reachable in the \\uses-DAG from lem:milne_codim1_indeterminacy (i.e. no orphan/island)? The milne proof \\uses now includes them — confirm.\n5. Any node marked \\leanok whose Lean is actually a sorry? (These four are sorry-free per the author; spot-check DifferenceMap.lean has no "sorry".)\n\nOutput data only.', { label: 'blueprint', phase: 'Verify', schema: SCHEMA }),
])

return results
